CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 24, 1955 reads: "Float at Matrons' Congress - When the Matrons' Congress A.A.O.O., Daughters of Sphinx, met in Pittsburgh Sunday, this was one of several floats which appeared in parade on Centre Avenue. Standing, left to right, are Verna Lightner, Queen Ovetta L. Johnson, Sarah Finch, Juanita Clark, Minnie Jones, Albertine Sellers, Josephine Minis, and Mary Alice McGee.  Seated: Ora Cooper, Lillie Goins, Mary E. White, president; Annie Mae Cherry.  Standing on the ground in front of the float is Laura E. Talley, organizer and vice president.-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Thirteen women, members of the Daughters of Sphinx, standing left to right; Verna Lightner, Ovetta L. Johnson, Sarah Finch, Juanita Clark, Minnie Jones, Albertine Sellers, Josephine Minis, and Mary Alice McGee, seated left to right; Ora Cooper, Lillie Goins, Mary E. White, Annie Mae Cherry, and Laura E. Talley standing in front of parade float with sign inscribed "Matrons Congress"
